# Code style (META)

**Imports**
- import-standards: Path aliases over relative; order: builtin → external → workspace → internal alias → relative; alphabetical within group.
- side-effect-imports: Only for polyfills and global styles; require explicit comment.

**Structure**
- one-responsibility-per-file: One responsibility per file; folder = domain or feature; no mixed abstractions in same folder.
- naming-folders-files: Folders kebab-case; React components PascalCase; hooks useCamelCase; utilities camelCase; configs kebab-case.

**Functions & classes**
- functions: Prefer pure; keep short; no hidden side effects.
- classes: Only for domain models and services; avoid god classes.

**Variables**
- variables: Prefer const; no var; meaningful names; single-letter only for loop indices.

**TypeScript**
- typescript-strict: Strict TS; no any; explicit return types for public functions.
- null-handling: Prefer undefined in app; null at DB boundary only; map in DTOs; optional chaining; avoid non-null assertions.

**Logging**
- logging: Structured logging; no console.log in production; include context (e.g. requestId, userId).

**Commits**
- commit-messages: Imperative present tense; descriptive of atomic change; optional prefixes feat fix docs chore refactor test; when using task graph use kebab-case task id as message.
